news.title: China's new home prices inch up for ninth month in May: Survey
news.para: The average new home price across 100 cities rose 0.25% on month in May, following a 0.27% gain in April, the data from real estate researcher China Index Academy showed on Saturday.

news.title: Puravankara's subsidiary acquires 12.75-acre land parcel in Thane
news.para: The land has an estimated potential carpet area of 18.20 lakh sq ft and a potential gross development value (GDV) of Rs 4,000 crore over the project lifecycle.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body ignores rampant building bylaw violations
news.para: Later, on October 11, 2023, the BBMP Assistant Executive Engineer, JP Nagar Subdivision, wrote letters to the Assistant Executive Engineer of the Bengaluru Water Supply and Sewerage Board (BWSSB), Jayanagar, to disconnect the water supply and sanitary connection to the building under construction at JP Nagar 2nd Stage.​

news.title: Properties registration in Mumbai up 22% in May: Knight Frank
news.para: ​Citing Maharashtra government data, Knight Frank India said Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) recorded around 12,000 property registrations last month as against 9,823 units in May last year.

news.title: Bosch leases 6.91 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru for expansion
news.para: The property is located at Life Science Park in Electronic City. Bosch will be paying rental at a rate of approximately ₹58 per sq ft with a binding agreement for five years with a hard option to extend by another five years, according to a lease registration document accessed by ET.

news.title: Suraksha Group all set to take over Jaypee Infratech
news.para: The move will take the Mumbai-based Suraksha Group a step closer to resuming construction on nine stalled projects of Wish Town in Noida and other locations and renew hopes for 20,000 buyers who invested in flats 15-20 years ago.

news.title: Court takes cognizance of ED chargesheet against Supreme Construction's director
news.para: It was allege that Supreme Construction & Developer Pvt Ltd(SCDPL), a company controlled by Tekchandani and others, collected Rs. 400 Crore from several homebuyers in a housing project in Taloja, Navi Mumbai.

news.title: China Evergrande Group fined $576 million for fraud: Regulator
news.para: China's deeply indebted property giant Evergrande has been fined $576 million for fraudulent business practices, Beijing's financial regulatory body said Friday.

news.title: House prices in UK rise by 0.4% in May 2024: Nationwide
news.para: Prices increased by 0.4% from April, the data showed, Compared with May last year, prices were 1.3% higher, a bigger increase than the median forecast in the Reuters poll for a 0.8% gain.

news.title: Investors rejoice: Surakshit Nivesh Yojna (PDPMY Phase-2) launches at Delhi Mall Complex
China’s 60 million homes are hard to sell even in big cities
news.para: China has the equivalent of 60 million unsold apartments, which will take more than four years to sell without government aid, according to Bloomberg Economics.

news.title: VACB refuses to conduct probe against Kerala CM in sand mining case
news.para: VACB declines to investigate petition linked to high court case on corruption charges. Concerns raised about corruption safe channels and legal jurisdictions.

news.title: China may impose record fine on PwC over Evergrande auditing work
news.para: China is set to impose a record fine on PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP and may suspend some of its local operations due to its involvement in a major financial fraud case with China Evergrande Group.

news.title: WeWork cleared to exit bankruptcy and slash $4 billion in debt
news.para: Flexible workspace provider WeWork expanded at breakneck speed but racked up steep losses on its over-extended real estate portfolio before filing for bankruptcy protection in November 2023.

news.title: Awfis Space Solutions shares close with over 9% gains in debut trade
news.para: On the NSE, Awfis Space Solutions shares climbed 9.2 per cent to settle at Rs 415.95 per piece. In volume terms, 1.36 crore equity shares were traded on the NSE.

news.title: EFC (I) posts net profit of Rs 27.93 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: EFC (I)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 99.11 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 63.14 per cent from Rs 60.75 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty posts net profit of Rs 101.33 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 434.99 crore in Q4 FY24 as against Rs 56.90 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Schneider Electric invests Rs 200 crore on 6.3 lakh sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: Deepak Sharma, zone president - Greater India, MD & CEO, Schneider Electric India, said, "It underlines our commitment to expanding our workforce of over 37,000 in India."
